		<div id="body_text">
			
			<p>The GenderMag Method consists of a gender-specialized cognitive walkthrough and a set of four GenderMag personas.</p>
            
			<h3>GenderMag Resources</h3>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Here is a <a href="./downloadables/genderMag-flyer.pdf">one-page flyer about GenderMag</a>.</li>
                <li>See the <a href="http://video.itu.dk/video/12452077/open-lecture-is-your-software-2">GenderMag talk</a> at IT University of Copenhagen, presented November 2015. Other talks and papers about GenderMag can be found <a href="http://web.engr.oregonstate.edu/~burnett/reprints.html">here</a>.</li>
                <li>Here's the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1NXjpj7NSGuVScPdR9EJgzv-eeKM9-NOY4gP9B0Dpf4U/viewform?edit_requested=true">kit</a> for using the method (beta version). The latest version is July 2017.  (Or, <a HREF="mailto:burnett@eecs.oregonstate.edu?subject=obtain GenderMag">request that a copy be sent to you via email</a> (2 MB).)</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Here are editable/customizable <a href="./downloadables/">personas and forms</a> in editable formats to use with the kit.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>The <a href="http://eusesconsortium.org/gender/GenderMagPersona-FoundationDocuments/Foundations.html">personas foundations document</a> is now available.  The latest version is Nov. 12, 2015.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Related Resources</h3>
            
            <ul>
                <li><a href="http://www.ncwit.org">National Center for Women in Technology (NCWIT)</a>: a great collection of resources on many aspects of gender and technology.</li>
                <li><a href="http://eusesconsortium.org/gender/genderRelated.php">Gender HCI Publications Resource</a> for those interested in Gender HCI research.</li>
                <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gender_HCI">Wikipedia Entry</a> on Gender HCI.</li>
            </ul>
			
